<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--
  index.html.j2 — Jinja2 template for the Nginx web page.

  Why show the hostname? So you can see which server HAProxy sent you to.
  Each of the three web nodes gets this same template deployed, but
  {{ inventory_hostname }} becomes "web01", "web02", or "web03" depending
  on which machine Ansible is configuring at that moment.

  Try refreshing your browser several times — you should cycle through all three.
-->
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>HA Lab — {{ inventory_hostname }}</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: monospace;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 80px auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
      background: #f4f4f4;
      color: #222;
    }
    h1 { font-size: 1.4rem; }
    .node {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #222;
      color: #7fff7f;
      padding: 6px 16px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }
    p { line-height: 1.6; }
    .tip { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>High Availability Lab</h1>

  <p>Served by: <span class="node">{{ inventory_hostname }}</span></p>

  <p>
    You're hitting one of three Nginx web nodes sitting behind an HAProxy
    load balancer. Each refresh may land on a different server.
  </p>

  <p class="tip">
    Try: <code>for i in {1..9}; do curl -s http://192.168.56.10 | grep "Served by"; done</code>
  </p>

  <p class="tip">
    Stop Nginx on this node with <code>sudo systemctl stop nginx</code> and
    watch HAProxy automatically remove it from rotation.
  </p>
</body>
</html>
